\f0\fs24\b CRM - Test Case Document\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1
\fs22\b 1. Authentication\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs20
1. Login page allows manual entry for Email field for Admin, Representative, Manager, and Field Officer. \b Pass\b0\par
2. Password field allows manual entry with masking. \b Pass\b0\par
3. Submitting with empty Email displays an error message and highlights the field. \b Fail\b0\par
4. Submitting with empty Password displays an error message and highlights the field. \b Fail\b0\par
5. Entering an invalid email format such as user@ shows a format validation error. \b Fail\b0\par
6. Entering incorrect credentials shows an invalid email or password error. \b Fail\b0\par
7. Clicking Forgot Password navigates to the Forgot Password page. \b Fail\b0\par
8. Successful login with valid credentials redirects the user to the role-based dashboard. \b Pass\b0\par
9. Logout clears the session token and redirects the user to the Login page. \b Pass\b0\par
\par
\fs22\b 2. Profile Management\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs20
1. User can update First Name, Last Name, and Contact Number manually. \b Pass\b0\par
2. Submitting the profile form with empty required fields shows error messages. \b Fail\b0\par
3. Upload Photo allows the user to browse and select an image file in JPG or PNG format. \b Pass\b0\par
4. The uploaded photo is previewed before saving and reflected in the header/sidebar after save. \b Fail\b0\par
5. Clicking Change Password reveals Current Password, New Password, and Confirm Password fields. \b Pass\b0\par
6. Submitting an incorrect current password shows a Current password is wrong error. \b Pass\b0\par
7. Submitting mismatched new and confirm passwords shows a validation error. \b Fail\b0\par
8. Successfully saving profile changes shows a success notification. \b Fail\b0\par
9. Clicking Logout logs the user out and redirects to the Login page. \b Pass\b0\par
\par
\fs22\b 3. MLA Role - Dashboard\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs20
1. The MLA Dashboard loads successfully after a valid login. \b Pass\b0\par
2. The dashboard displays the correct summary cards for grievances, resolved cases, pending cases, and sentiment status. \b Pass\b0\par
3. The dashboard shows the latest alerts and notifications for the MLA user. \b Fail\b0\par
4. The KPI cards for the poll are displayed and functioning correctly. \b Fail\b0\par
5. Selecting a constituency updates all dashboard widgets and charts correctly. \b Pass\b0\par
6. Applying a date range filter shows only the records within the selected period. \b Pass\b0\par
7. Clicking a grievance from the dashboard opens its detailed information page. \b Fail\b0\par
8. The sentiment analysis section displays the correct trend for public feedback. \b Pass\b0\par
9. The complaint trend chart reflects the latest grievance submissions and resolutions. \b Pass\b0\par
10. The dashboard updates automatically when new grievances are added. \b Pass\b0\par
11. The ward-wise map or location view highlights areas with high complaint volume. \b Pass\b0\par
12. Grievances are sorted and displayed correctly according to priority. \b Pass\b0\par
13. Exporting the dashboard report generates a downloadable file with the correct data. \b Fail\b0\par
14. Clicking a chart segment opens the related list of grievances. \b Fail\b0\par
15. Changing the status filter updates the counts and listed grievances correctly. \b Pass\b0\par
16. The system displays a user-friendly error message when the backend data load fails. \b Fail\b0\par
17. Logging out from the MLA Dashboard redirects the user to the login page. \b Pass\b0\par
\par
